FBIS3-39242 "drweu031__a94026" FBIS-WEU-94-031-A Document Type:Daily Report 15 Feb 1994 ANNEX Italy Kidnappers Release Italian Workers in Somalia BR1502115694 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1141 GMT 15 Feb 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY BR1502115694 Rome ANSAMAIL Database Language: English Article Type:BFN [Unattributed article: "Italian Hostages in Somalia Released"] [Text] Rome, 15 Feb (ANSA) -- Two Italian relief workers kidnapped Sunday [13 February] north of Mogadishu and held by Somali herdsmen demanding ransom of 50,000 dollars have been released, Defense Minister Fabio Fabbri reported here. The men, Gianfranco Stefani, 46, and Sergio Passadore, 38, were abducted near Giohar, 80 kilometers north of Mogadishu. They are on the staff of Cefa, (the European Consortium for Agricultural Training) and were working on a farm development project in the Giohar area at the time of the kidnap.
